original_title: Australian MPs at Sri Lankan food fair in Sydney
original_body_lines: Australian MPs Warren Kirby and Julian Leeser were among those who attended a Sri Lankan food fair held in Sydney organized by the Sri Lankan Catholic Association of New South Wales yesterday (Saturday).
The Daily Mirror was the official online media partner for the event.
The fair was held at the Don Moore Community Centre, North Rocks NSW Australia.
Besides a variety of delicious traditional street food dishes as well as sweets and snacks, there was also musical entertainment and raffle prizes.

Proceeds of the fair will go towards supporting local charity initiatives as well as very deserving charitable causes in Sri Lanka. Some of those affected by the Easter Sunday massacre will also be supported.
